<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14063">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Basketry.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5831">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5831 mb-requirement-id-5832">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to
        encounter while using basketry tools and materials, and what you should
        do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nhB-42oMZF8" target="_blank"
          >Cutting Tool Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jIllqEyw3rA" target="_blank"
          >Hand Tool Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://sites.google.com/basketweavers.org/missouribasketweaversguild/weaving-tips/health-and-safety"
          target="_blank"
          >Health and Safety Tips for Basket Weavers (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5831 mb-requirement-id-5833">
        (b) Discuss the prevention of and first-aid treatment for injuries,
        including cuts, scratches, and scrapes, that could occur while working
        with basketry tools and materials. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/L77rERL64zc" target="_blank"
          >How to Treat Cuts &amp; Scrapes | First Aid Training (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5824">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5824 mb-requirement-id-5825">
        (a) Show your counselor that you are able to identify the following
        types of baskets: plaited, coiled, ribbed, and wicker.<br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.wicker-basket.co.uk/blogs/news/what-are-the-four-types-of-baskets/"
          target="_blank"
          >What Are the Four Types of Baskets? (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Z5PttnxrB0I" target="_blank"
          >Historical Types of Baskets (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5824 mb-requirement-id-5826">
        (b) Describe three different types of weaves to your counselor. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/knbR3kgGssE" target="_blank"
          >How to Start a Coiled Basket (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Jb0tFaZytM8" target="_blank"
          >Making a Ribbed Basket (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/yqe6R4uWzQo" target="_blank"
          >Weaving a Plaited Bsket (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5827">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Plan and weave the following projects:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5827 mb-requirement-id-5828">
        (a) Square basket <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2H0VJtOZ-Kk" target="_blank"
          >Bamboo Basket Tokari Weaving (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5827 mb-requirement-id-5829">
        (b) Round basket <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gKYft82Yobk" target="_blank"
          >How to Make a Rustic Round Basket out of Wild Vines (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jnK1kUcXqO0" target="_blank"
          >Round Reed Basket (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/e-ZFtsLuiMo" target="_blank"
          >Cherokee Basket Weaving (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5827 mb-requirement-id-5830">
        (c) Campstool seat <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qdtWwXhm0H8" target="_blank"
          >Weaving a Camp Stool (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/k9jRWXz8HOs" target="_blank"
          >Learn to Rope Your Chairs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/e_boV4f5tp4" target="_blank"
          >How to Weave a Wooden Chair Step by Step (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
